[{"_path":"/docs/node/mining-mode","_dir":"node","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Mining Mode","description":"The Beam Node supports External Miner via Stratum Server API for mining Beam: The Beam Node provides built-in support for Stratum API integration with multiple external mining clients to a single node.\nStratum clients can be run together with the internal Miner. For more detailed information, and how-to mine Beam, please see our Beam Mining guide.","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"mining-mode"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining Mode"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Beam Node supports External Miner via Stratum Server API for mining Beam: The Beam Node provides built-in support for Stratum API integration with multiple external mining clients to a single node.\nStratum clients can be run together with the internal Miner. For more detailed information, and how-to mine Beam, please see our "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://beam.mw/en/docs/mining/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Beam Mining guide"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{% hint style=\"info\" %}\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Obtain your Miner Keys!"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To ensure all the rewards you accrue mining Beam go directly to your wallet, you must obtain your secret "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"miner_key"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":". Your mining key is derived from your seed phrase. You can generate multiple mining keys for separate mining modes."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conversely, to display your total mining rewards accrued to all the nodes on the Beam network, you must obtain an "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"owner_key"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Owner keys only identify the cumulative mining rewards earned by a user, regardless of the node used."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For more information on retrieving or displaying mining and owner keys, please see our Beam Mining guide_._\n{% endhint %}"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"mining-beam"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining Beam"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Beam is a Mimblewimble implementation. We use classic Proof-of-Work (PoW) consensus."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Alike most cryptocurrencies, Beam relies on miners to add transactions to the blockchain. While all nodes in the Beam network confirm the validity of transactions, Beam counts on miners to take on the massive heavy lifting to guard the network."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We welcome everyone to join our mining community to support the network and earn Beam coins."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"mining-algorithm"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining algorithm"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To secure the network, Beam uses the uses a "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://docs.beam.mw/Beam_Equihash.pdf","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"modified version"}]},{"type":"text","value":" of the Equihash (150,5) proof-of-work mining algorithm. Miners and their mining rigs compete to produce a new block on the chain. The miner who completes the computation for each block earns a network standard block reward, including any transactions fees added to that block."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At Mainnet launch, the Equihash parameters were: n=150, k=5. In addition, we will introduce a slight change to the datapath to further reduce the chance of zero-day ASICs."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The minimal memory requirement for the GPU is 4 GB. The most up-to-date list of supported GPUs will be made "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"broken-reference"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"available"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"block-size-and-time"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Block size and time"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A Beam block will be generated approximately every minute and contain about 1000 transactions. Block size is roughly 1 MB."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"mining-difficulty"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining difficulty"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One can define 'difficulty' as the inverse probability of a random solution being the correct one. Mining difficulty measures how many attempts, on average, it is required to find the necessary proof-of-work solution to mine a block and receive the mining reward. Thus, a difficulty of 100 means that (on average) one in 100 tries should produce a valid block."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Proof of Work blockchains, the difficulty is a dynamic parameter, periodically retargeted to reflect the fluctuations in all the miners' total computational power while accounting for changes in the mining competition and improvements in mining technology."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The goal of updating the difficulty is to keep the average block time at a certain value. In Beam, the target block time is 60 seconds, which underpins a constant currency issuance and the transaction settlement time of the network."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here's an example: let's assume we have 100 miners in our network, each attempting a different solution, finding one roughly every minute. Now 100 more miners enter, the hash rate of the network doubles, the solution on average reduces by half (30 seconds). If 200 more join, the time halves into 15 seconds, and so on."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Beam nodes attempt to mitigate that by increasing the difficulting of the proof-of-work algorithm as more miners join, reducing the difficulty as the number of miners decreases."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Beam, the difficulty reassess with every block: the algorithm looks at the average time and the average difficulty of the last 1440 blocks. If the time required to mine the previous 1440 blocks is higher or lower than 24 hours, the problem retargets accordingly."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The detailed algorithm is outlined below:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Review the last seven blocks, identifying the block with the median block time, this is the "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window End block"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Review blocks from 127 to 120 before the current block (seven blocks total), identifying the block with the median block time out of those, this is the "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window Start block"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sum the difficulties of the blocks from "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window Start"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window End"}]},{"type":"text","value":"; this is "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Work"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Calculate the time difference between "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window Start"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Window End"}]},{"type":"text","value":" blocks; this is "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Time"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Calculate the difficulty for next block as: "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NewDifficulty"}]},{"type":"text","value":" = ("},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Work"}]},{"type":"text","value":" / "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Time"}]},{"type":"text","value":") * 60 seconds."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Time"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is bound by one and 4 hours; e.g., it is considered "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Delta Time"}]},{"type":"text","value":" if the difference is less than one hour. Same for differences more than 4 hours, preventing extreme changes in difficulty."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The above algorithm ensures that as the total solution power of the network fluctuates, the difficulty is gradually adjusted, ensuring the target block time."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"treasury"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Treasury"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For the first five years of Beam's emission schedule, block rewards will allocate to the Beam Treasury (along with miners) for every block mined."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"‌During year one, the Treasury receives 20 Beam coins per block. In years 2-5, 10 coins per block will go to the Treasury."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The purpose of the Treasury is to repay Beam investors, incentivize the core development team, but the most significant single beneficiary of the Treasury will be the Beam Foundation."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The distribution of the Treasury Coins will occur monthly in the following amounts:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Investors"}]},{"type":"text","value":": 40%"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core Team"}]},{"type":"text","value":": 40%"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Beam Foundation"}]},{"type":"text","value":": 20% (Biggest single beneficiary)."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"asic-resistance"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ASIC resistance"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Beam plans to keep mining ASIC resistant through the first 18 months to establish decentralization by performing one hard fork after six months and then a second hard fork after 12 months of Beams emission. Each hard fork will tweak the mining algorithm, the modifications releasing several weeks prior."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"mining-guide"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://beam.mw/docs/mining/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining guide"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"See our "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://beam.mw/docs/mining/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"mining guide"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for more information on how-to mine Beam coins."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"mining-using-external-miner"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mining using external miner"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This guide will walk you through organizing a mining rig using a stand-alone Beam node, Stratum server, and mining client."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Before using the external miner, please review the sample Mining Architecture below:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"Mining usiex","src":".gitbook/assets/image.png"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"ty